 592, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ourPrivacy notice\", \"from\": 443, \"to\": 460}, {\"ngram\": \"Peatyhas\", \"from\": 481, \"to\": 489}, {\"ngram\": \"a breakdown\", \"from\": 537, \"to\": 548}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"deep, dark hole\", \"from\": 571, \"to\": 589}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peaty reached a low last February when he pulled himself out of the pool where he trained inLoughborough, telling his coach he could not continue.\", \"from\": 594, \"to\": 740, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Peaty\", \"from\": 594, \"to\": 599}, {\"ngram\": \"a low last February\", \"from\": 608, \"to\": 627}, {\"ngram\": \"the pool\", \"from\": 658, \"to\": 666}, {\"ngram\": \"inLoughborough\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 698}, {\"ngram\": \"his coach\", \"from\": 708, \"to\": 717}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The breaststroke extraordinaire was the first British swimmer to win thegold medalin the 100m breaststroke at the 2016 Olympics, and again at the 2020 Olympics, and boasted an unbeaten record between 2014 and 2022.\", \"from\": 742, \"to\": 956, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 788, \"end\": 795, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.7060442766990831, \"rank\": 0.3968444479757055, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The breaststroke extraordinaire\", \"from\": 742, \"to\": 773}, {\"ngram\": \"thegold medalin\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 826}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2016 Olympics\", \"from\": 852, \"to\": 869}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2020 Olympics\", \"from\": 884, \"to\": 901}, {\"ngram\": \"an unbeaten record\", \"from\": 915, \"to\": 933}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2022, he returned to the pool too quickly after breaking his foot, leading to his first ever defeat, and he separated from his partner Eirianedd Munro, the mother of his three-year-old son, George-Anderson.\", \"from\": 958, \"to\": 1167, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1106, \"end\": 1111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munro\", \"score\": 0.987102515935635, \"rank\": 0.013065799612073362, \"text\": \"Munro\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munro\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the pool\", \"from\": 982, \"to\": 990}, {\"ngram\": \"his foot\", \"from\": 1018, \"to\": 1026}, {\"ngram\": \"his first ever defeat\", \"from\": 1039, \"to\": 1060}, {\"ngram\": \"his partner\", \"from\": 1084, \"to\": 1095}, {\"ngram\": \"the mother\", \"from\": 1113, \"to\": 1123}, {\"ngram\": \"his three-year-old son\", \"from\": 1127, \"to\": 1149}, {\"ngram\": \"George-Anderson\", \"from\": 1151, \"to\": 1166}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The following year, he met Holly Ramsay, 24, the model and influencer daughter of Gordon, 57, the renowned TV chef and mentor who helped the 29-year-old recover.\", \"from\": 1169, \"to\": 1330, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1196, \"end\": 1201, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holly_Cunningham\", \"score\": 0.8787897281274755, \"rank\": 0.13792863978068184, \"text\": \"Holly\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holly_Cunningham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holly_Cunningham\"}, {\"begin\": 1202, \"end\": 1208, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Ramsay\", \"score\": 0.9948614924749938, \"rank\": 0.0036504807839654765, \"text\": \"Ramsay\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Ramsay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Ramsay\"}, {\"begin\": 1251, \"end\": 1257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Gordon\", \"score\": 0.9763268798056639, \"rank\": 0.024245942937520148, \"text\": \"Gordon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Gordon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Gordon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the model and influencer daughter\", \"from\": 1214, \"to\": 1247}, {\"ngram\": \"the renowned TV chef\", \"from\": 1263, \"to\": 1283}, {\"ngram\": \"mentor\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1294}, {\"ngram\": \"the 29-year-old recover\", \"from\": 1306, \"to\": 1329}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peaty toldThe Sunday Times:\\\"He's an incredible energy to be around and an incredible person to have that guidance from.\\\"\", \"from\": 1332, \"to\": 1452, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Peaty toldThe Sunday Times:\\\"He's an incredible energy\", \"from\": 1332, \"to\": 1385}, {\"ngram\": \"an incredible person\", \"from\": 1403, \"to\": 1423}, {\"ngram\": \"that guidance\", \"from\": 1432, \"to\": 1445}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He says he shares similar qualities with Ramsay, who worked his way up to the top of his industry with relentless presfessionalism.\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1585, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1495, \"end\": 1501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Ramsay\", \"score\": 0.9948614924749938, \"rank\": 0.0036504807839654765, \"text\": \"Ramsay\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Ramsay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Ramsay\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"similar qualities\", \"from\": 1472, \"to\": 1489}, {\"ngram\": \"his way\", \"from\": 1514, \"to\": 1521}, {\"ngram\": \"the top\", \"from\": 1528, \"to\": 1535}, {\"ngram\": \"his industry\", \"from\": 1539, \"to\": 1551}, {\"ngram\": \"relentless presfessionalism\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1584}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Inspired by Ramsay's composure, Peaty told the outlet he has changed how he operates.\", \"from\": 1587, \"to\": 1672, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1599, \"end\": 1605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Ramsay\", \"score\": 0.9948614924749938, \"rank\": 0.0036504807839654765, \"text\": \"Ramsay\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Ramsay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Ramsay\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Peaty\", \"from\": 1619, \"to\": 1624}, {\"ngram\": \"the outlet\", \"from\": 1630, \"to\": 1640}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Holly, Ramsay's second eldest child, has also opened up in the past about her mental health struggles, the 24-year-old was diagnosed with PTSD, anxiety and depression after a sexual assault when she was 18 years old led her to be admitted ot a psychiatric hospital.\", \"from\": 1674, \"to\": 1939, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1681, \"end\": 1687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Ramsay\", \"score\": 0.9948614924749938, \"rank\": 0.0036504807839654765, \"text\": \"Ramsay\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Ramsay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Ramsay\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the past\", \"from\": 1733, \"to\": 1741}, {\"ngram\": \"her mental health struggles\", \"from\": 1748, \"to\": 1775}, {\"ngram\": \"PTSD\", \"from\": 1812, \"to\": 1816}, {\"ngram\": \"anxiety\", \"from\": 1818, \"to\": 1825}, {\"ngram\": \"depression\", \"from\": 1830, \"to\": 1840}, {\"ngram\": \"a sexual assault\", \"from\": 1847, \"to\": 1863}, {\"ngram\": \"a psychiatric hospital\", \"from\": 1916, \"to\": 1938}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peaty says Holly gives him \\\"peace and stability\\\" and that they bonded straight away, the swimmer even has the letter \\\"H\\\" tattooed behind his ear to honour their relationship.\", \"from\": 1941, \"to\": 2115, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Peaty\", \"from\": 1941, \"to\": 1946}, {\"ngram\": \"Holly\", \"from\": 1952, \"to\": 1957}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"peace\", \"from\": 1968, \"to\": 1974}, {\"ngram\": \"stability\", \"from\": 1979, \"to\": 1988}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimmer\", \"from\": 2026, \"to\": 2037}, {\"ngram\": \"the letter \\\"H\\\" tattooed\", \"from\": 2047, \"to\": 2070}, {\"ngram\": \"his ear\", \"from\": 2078, \"to\": 2085}, {\"ngram\": \"their relationship\", \"from\": 2096, \"to\": 2114}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking of the day he broke down, the gold medal swimmer revealed he walked out of his training practice teary-eyed, something he had never done before, and went to the shop to buy an entire basket of chocolate, since he had also had to follow a strict regime.\", \"from\": 2117, \"to\": 2378, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the day\", \"from\": 2129, \"to\": 2136}, {\"ngram\": \"the gold medal swimmer\", \"from\": 2152, \"to\": 2174}, {\"ngram\": \"his training practice\", \"from\": 2201, \"to\": 2222}, {\"ngram\": \"the shop\", \"from\": 2283, \"to\": 2291}, {\"ngram\": \"an entire basket\", \"from\": 2299, \"to\": 2315}, {\"ngram\": \"chocolate\", \"from\": 2319, \"to\": 2328}, {\"ngram\": \"a strict regime\", \"from\": 2362, \"to\": 2377}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He told the outlet: \\\"I'd felt like a God on so many occasions.\", \"from\": 2380, \"to\": 2442, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the outlet\", \"from\": 2388, \"to\": 2398}, {\"ngram\": \"a God\", \"from\": 2415, \"to\": 2420}, {\"ngram\": \"so many occasions\", \"from\": 2424, \"to\": 2441}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now I felt like a complete failure who'd let everyone down.\", \"from\": 2443, \"to\": 2502, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a complete failure\", \"from\": 2459, \"to\": 2477}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 2488, \"to\": 2496}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I'd achieved everything, met every goal but in doing that I just kept moving the bar higher and higher.\", \"from\": 2504, \"to\": 2608, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 2518, \"to\": 2528}, {\"ngram\": \"every goal\", \"from\": 2534, \"to\": 2544}, {\"ngram\": \"the bar\", \"from\": 2582, \"to\": 2589}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When it all became too much I started drinking.\", \"from\": 2609, \"to\": 2656, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was good to feel numb for a while but that's just the starting point in that downward spiral.\", \"from\": 2657, \"to\": 2753, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"just the starting point\", \"from\": 2705, \"to\": 2728}, {\"ngram\": \"that downward spiral\", \"from\": 2732, \"to\": 2752}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Life lost its colour, its fun and joy.\\\"\", \"from\": 2754, \"to\": 2793, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Life\", \"from\": 2754, \"to\": 2758}, {\"ngram\": \"its colour\", \"from\": 2764, \"to\": 2774}, {\"ngram\": \"its fun\", \"from\": 2776, \"to\": 2783}, {\"ngram\": \"joy\", \"from\": 2788, \"to\": 2791}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When his \\\"dam finally burst\\\", Peaty says finding church and working with psychiatrist Steve Peters also helped aid his recovery from burnout.\", \"from\": 2795, \"to\": 2936, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2881, \"end\": 2893, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Peters_(Ontario_politician)\", \"score\": 0.7088566847014273, \"rank\": 0.1305803571429046, \"text\": \"Steve Peters\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Peters_(Ontario_politician)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Peters_(Ontario_politician)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his \\\"dam\", \"from\": 2800, \"to\": 2808}, {\"ngram\": \"Peaty\", \"from\": 2825, \"to\": 2830}, {\"ngram\": \"church\", \"from\": 2844, \"to\": 2850}, {\"ngram\": \"his recovery\", \"from\": 2910, \"to\": 2922}, {\"ngram\": \"burnout\", \"from\": 2928, \"to\": 2935}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He says he is no longer driven by emotion after his unbeaten streak from 2014 to 2022 was achieved by \\\"seeing red\\\", adding that he now knows when to pick the best moments to channel rage for \\\"real moments of battle\\\".\", \"from\": 2938, \"to\": 3154, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"emotion\", \"from\": 2972, \"to\": 2979}, {\"ngram\": \"his unbeaten streak\", \"from\": 2986, \"to\": 3005}, {\"ngram\": \"red\", \"from\": 3048, \"to\": 3051}, {\"ngram\": \"the best moments\", \"from\": 3092, \"to\": 3108}, {\"ngram\": \"rage\", \"from\": 3120, \"to\": 3124}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"real moments\", \"from\": 3129, \"to\": 3142}, {\"ngram\": \"battle\", \"from\": 3146, \"to\": 3152}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peaty will compete in the 2024 Paris Olympics after a momentous victory at 100m breaststroke GB Swimming Championships where he set the fastest time of the year.\", \"from\": 3156, \"to\": 3317, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3249, \"end\": 3251, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.7365254296596843, \"rank\": 0.35771012109755423, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 3252, \"end\": 3260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.7295460112928664, \"rank\": 0.3696359679727752, \"text\": \"Swimming\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_2008_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Peaty\", \"from\": 3156, \"to\": 3161}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 3178, \"to\": 3201}, {\"ngram\": \"a momentous victory\", \"from\": 3208, \"to\": 3227}, {\"ngram\": \"the fastest time\", \"from\": 3288, \"to\": 3304}, {\"ngram\": \"the year\", \"from\": 3308, \"to\": 3316}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If he achieves gold this summer he will belong to the same camp as Michael Phelps, as the only male swimmers to have gained gold in the same event at three Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 3319, \"to\": 3489, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3386, \"end\": 3400, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.493145859071157e-37, \"text\": \"Michael Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 3334, \"to\": 3338}, {\"ngram\": \"the same camp\", \"from\": 3369, \"to\": 3382}, {\"ngram\": \"the only male swimmers\", \"from\": 3405, \"to\": 3427}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 3443, \"to\": 3447}, {\"ngram\": \"the same event\", \"from\": 3451, \"to\": 3465}, {\"ngram\": \"three Olympic Games\", \"from\": 3469, \"to\": 3488}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If you are experiencing feelings of distress, or are struggling to cope, you can speak to the Samaritans, in confidence, on 116 123 (UK and ROI), email jo@samaritans.org, or visit theSamaritanswebsite to find details of your nearest branch.\", \"from\": 3491, \"to\": 3731, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3585, \"end\": 3595, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samaritans\", \"score\": 0.9999577146022796, \"rank\": 3.1252954601825916e-05, \"text\": \"Samaritans\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samaritans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samaritans\"}, {\"begin\": 3624, \"end\": 3626, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9996171247018558, \"rank\": 0.00038078799213996225, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"feelings\", \"from\": 3515, \"to\": 3523}, {\"ngram\": \"distress\", \"from\": 3527, \"to\": 3535}, {\"ngram\": \"confidence\", \"from\": 3600, \"to\": 3610}, {\"ngram\": \"ROI\", \"from\": 3631, \"to